WorkItem.ClosedComment: This has been fixed in the latest version of the spec
WorkItem.Description:
Chapter 9.4 describes that EnumMemberAssignments are transpiled into something like

```
Color[Color.Red = 0] = "Red"; 
```

There is also a TODO describing that string access should generally be used. However, Typescript does already compile it to

```
Color[Color["Red"] = 0] = "Red"; 
```

This renders both the example wrong and the TODO (at least in that spot) obsolete.
